@startuml
title Sequence Diagram: File Upload (with Pipeline Replication)

actor Client
participant "Metadata Server\n(Master)" as Master
participant "Storage Node A\n(Primary)" as SN_A
participant "Storage Node B\n(Replica)" as SN_B
participant "Storage Node C\n(Replica)" as SN_C

== 1. Authorization & Allocation ==
Client -> Master: Request Upload (Filename, Size, Auth Token)
activate Master
Master -> Master: Validate Token\n& Check Quota
Master -> Master: Calculate Chunks\n& Select 3 Storage Nodes
Master --> Client: Authorized (FileID, Chunk 1 -> Nodes: A, B, C)
deactivate Master

== 2. Data Transfer (TCP Binary Stream) ==
note over Client, SN_A: TCP connection opens
Client -> SN_A: Send Chunk 1 Data + Replica List (B, C)
activate SN_A

note over SN_A, SN_B: Pipeline forwarding
SN_A -> SN_B: Forward Chunk 1 Data + Replica List (C)
activate SN_B

SN_B -> SN_C: Forward Chunk 1 Data
activate SN_C
note over SN_C: Saves to Disk
SN_C --> SN_B: ACK (Saved)
deactivate SN_C

note over SN_B: Saves to Disk
SN_B --> SN_A: ACK (Saved & Replicated)
deactivate SN_B

note over SN_A: Saves to Disk
SN_A --> Client: ACK (Chunk 1 Uploaded to all 3 nodes)
deactivate SN_A

== 3. Metadata Commit ==
Client -> Master: Confirm Upload Complete (FileID)
activate Master
Master -> Master: Commit to Database\n(File status: Available)
Master --> Client: 200 OK (File visible in cluster)
deactivate Master

@enduml
